      "description": "Available is a museum-quality 2011 BMW M3 (E92), a pinnacle of naturally aspirated engineering. Power is derived from the S65 4.0L V8, featuring eight individual throttle bodies and a surgical 8,400 RPM redline. This example is mechanically pristine, with documented preventative rod bearing service and a rigid, crack-free subframe. The 6-speed manual gearbox provides direct mechanical linkage to the variable M differential, ensuring precise torque distribution and maximum corner-exit traction. Equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC), the suspension geometry and damping rates remain true to factory specifications. The exterior displays factory-perfect paint depth with zero oxidation, while the cabin retains the original matte finish on all Novillo leather touchpoints. A truly unmolested, turn-key performance icon for the discerning collector.",
